Severstal Drops for 4th Day After Steel Output Slides 5 Percent

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-04-28T09:26:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/severstal-drops-for-4th-day-after-steel-output-slides-5-percent.html
OAO Severstal slipped for the
fourth day after Russian billionaire  Alexei Mordashov ’s
steelmaker said crude steel output fell 5 percent in the first
quarter from the previous three months to 3.65 million metric
tons.  The stock declined 0.8 percent to 510.6 rubles by 1:15 p.m.
in Moscow.  Gold sales at Severstal’s unit, Nord Gold NV, dropped 10
percent to 173,930 ounces. 